# GoCmsCheck - Change Log

## Overview
GoCmsCheck is a CMS security scanner that supports WordPress and Drupal. This file documents all changes, features, and implementations for future reference.

---

## v1.0.1 (Current)

### New Features

**WordPress Scanning:**
- **Bundled plugin list**: 100 common WordPress plugin slugs embedded at compile time via `//go:embed`
- **Plugin scanning workflow**: Check bundled list first against WPVulnerability API, then dynamically parse HTML for additional plugins not already found
- **Deduplication**: Plugins found in the bundled list are not re-checked during HTML parsing

### Bug Fixes

**HTTP Client:**
- `DoRequest` now accepts an `io.Reader` body parameter, enabling proper POST requests with payloads
- `Post()` method fixed to actually send the request body (previously sent `nil`)
- Removed duplicated rate-limiting/retry logic from `Post()` (now delegates to `DoRequest`)

**WordPress Pingback:**
- `PerformPingbackCheck`: Fixed bug where XML-RPC pingback body was never sent to the server
- `CheckXmlRpc`: Fixed bug where XML-RPC method list request body was never sent to the server
- Removed unused `http.Request` variables that were constructed but discarded
- Pingback check now only runs when XML-RPC is enabled (no misleading output when XML-RPC is blocked)
- Non-200 responses from `xmlrpc.php` now report meaningful errors (e.g., "XML-RPC blocked (HTTP 405)")
- Report shows `[-] Pingback disabled: <reason>` when pingback is blocked instead of showing nothing

---

## v1.0.0

### Features Implemented

**WordPress Scanning:**
- Version detection (meta tags, CSS paths, HTML)
- Plugin detection from HTML source
- Theme detection from HTML paths
- Login endpoint verification (`/wp-login.php`, `/wp-admin`)
- XML-RPC analysis and method listing
- Pingback vulnerability testing
- WPVulnerability API integration with caching

**Drupal Scanning:**
- Version detection (meta tags, CHANGELOG.txt)
- Module and theme detection from HTML
- Login/admin endpoint checks
- Node enumeration (1-100) at 5 req/s
- User enumeration (1-100) at 5 req/s
- Configuration file checks (`.yml` files)
- OSV.dev API integration with caching

**Performance:**
- Global rate limiting at 5 requests/second
- In-memory cache for vulnerability API responses
- Node enumeration limited to 100 nodes for performance
- User enumeration limited to 100 users for performance
- Total max scan time: ~2 minutes

**Color Output:**
- Uses `github.com/fatih/color` v1.18.0 for colored terminal output
- **Stdout**: Colored output with ANSI codes
  - Bold cyan for section headers
  - Bold for labels and prefixes (e.g., `[+] Found endpoint:`, `Version:`, `[+] Plugins found:`)
  - Normal text for data/content
- **File Output**: Plain text (ANSI codes stripped via `stripANSICodes()`)

**Output & Reporting:**
- **No default output file** - use `--output <filename>` to save report

### Command Line Flags
- `--url <URL>`: Target URL (required)
- `--cms <wordpress|drupal>`: CMS type (optional)
- `--output <filename>`: Save report to file (optional)
- `--all-plugins`: Scan all plugins (default: top 10)
- `--all-modules`: Scan all modules (default: top 10)
- `--server <url>`: Pingback test server (WordPress only)
- `--help`: Show usage information

### Usage Examples
```bash
# WordPress scan (stdout only, colored)
./goCmsCheck --url example.com --cms wordpress

# WordPress scan with file output (plain text)
./goCmsCheck --url example.com --cms wordpress --output wp_report.txt

# Drupal scan (stdout only, colored)
./goCmsCheck --url example.com --cms drupal

# Drupal scan with file output (plain text)
./goCmsCheck --url example.com --cms drupal --output drupal_report.txt

# Full module scan
./goCmsCheck --url example.com --cms drupal --all-modules --output report.txt
```

### Files Modified/Created
- `internal/scanner/plugins.txt` - **New**: 100 common WordPress plugin slugs
- `internal/scanner/wordpress.go` - Added `//go:embed`, `LoadBundledPlugins()`, updated plugin scanning workflow; fixed pingback/XML-RPC body sending; added XML-RPC guard for pingback
- `internal/scanner/httpclient.go` - Modified `DoRequest` signature to accept body; simplified `Post` method
- `internal/report/report.go` - Added pingback disabled feedback output
- `CHANGELOG` - Updated with new features and bug fixes
- `cmd/goCmsCheck/main.go` - Main entry point, flag handling
- `internal/scanner/drupal.go` - Drupal scanning logic
- `internal/report/report.go` - Report generation with fatih/color output
- `README.md` - Project documentation with examples
- `go.mod` - Added github.com/fatih/color v1.18.0 dependency
- `go.sum` - Updated with fatih/color v1.18.0 and transitive dependencies

### Testing
- Tested against WordPress target: `https://www.armourinfosec.test`
- Tested against Drupal target: `http://drupal.test`
- Verified stdout color output with fatih/color
- Verified file output is plain text (no ANSI codes)
- Verified no default file is created without `--output` flag
- Verified go.mod and go.sum updated with fatih/color v1.18.0
- Verified dependency chain: fatih/color → go-colorable → go-isatty → go-sys
- Verified --output flag is optional (no default value)

